# CPU Scheduling Algorithms Simulator

A C implementation of classic CPU scheduling algorithms, built as part of an OS course project.

## Algorithms implemented

| Algorithm | Type |
|---|---|
| FCFS | Non-preemptive |
| SJF | Non-preemptive |
| SRTF | Preemptive (shortest remaining time first) |
| Priority | Preemptive |
| Priority | Non-preemptive |
| Round Robin | Preemptive |
| Multilevel Queue | — |

Each algorithm outputs a Gantt chart and a results table showing completion time, turnaround time, waiting time, and response time for every process.

## How to compile

```bash
gcc -o main main.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/miltilevel_queue.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/FCFS.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/SJF.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/PRIORITYPRE.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/PRIOTITY_NONPRE.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/SRTF.c \
    Scheduling_Algorithms/ROUND_ROBIN.c \
    utils.c \
    Priority_queue.c \
    Queue.c
```

## How to run

```bash
./main
```

You will be prompted to enter the number of processes and their details (arrival time, burst time, priority).

## File structure

```
.
├── main.c                            # entry point, process input and algorithm selection
├── Algorithms.h                      # shared function declarations
├── process.h                         # Process struct definition
├── utils.c / utils.h                 # result printing and helpers
├── Queue.c / Priority_queue.c        # queue data structures
└── Scheduling_Algorithms/
    ├── FCFS.c
    ├── SJF.c
    ├── SRTF.c
    ├── PRIORITYPRE.c
    ├── PRIOTITY_NONPRE.c
    ├── ROUND_ROBIN.c
    └── miltilevel_queue.c
```
